{"id": "EUVD-2022-55518", "enisaUuid": "6ebd4afc-6770-30c7-97bc-3172ab606e18", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nocxl: fix pci device refcount leak when calling get_function_0()\n\nget_function_0() calls pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot(), as comment\nsays, it returns a pci device with refcount increment, so after\nusing it, pci_dev_put() needs be called.\n\nGet the device reference when get_function_0() is not called, so\npci_dev_put() can be called in the error path and callers\nunconditionally. And add comment above get_dvsec_vendor0() to tell\ncallers to call pci_dev_put().", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-04T15:30:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a40e1b0a922a53fa925ea8b296e3de30a31ed028", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/37a13b274e4513c757e50c002ddcbf4bc89adbb2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9a1b3148975b71fdc194e62612478346bbe618cd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/40ff4c2335a98f0ee96b099bfd70b8e6644f321f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/27158c72678b39ee01cc01de1aba6b51c71abe2f", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50337"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50337"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0c4af846-5a17-3908-ba03-42295cb0d8a3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "87db7579ebd5ded337056eb765542eb2608f16e3 <9a1b3148975b71fdc194e62612478346bbe618cd"}, {"id": "1196ed9b-4a52-3dff-87db-dc71613775be", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "1838936e-dc9e-38d5-8e47-6bf39408dc7b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "1d3126fc-fa14-3448-9ff0-b252585a6b34", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "87db7579ebd5ded337056eb765542eb2608f16e3 <a40e1b0a922a53fa925ea8b296e3de30a31ed028"}, {"id": "49b8cb8e-5fc7-3c57-a557-f83cca879b9e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.9"}, {"id": "69bfc32b-52cc-33c6-8cde-2b59ff43